432, 539.0369, 541.6998, 543.289, 542.2833, 542.7784, 543.1662, 544.7265, 545.1511, 545.9104, 545.218, 544.544, 543.3418, 542.8852, 543.5366, 544.4346, 542.1815, 542.9912, 542.3729, 542.506, 543.1201, 544.6278, 545.4856, 546.5731, 546.6666, 545.8557, 546.7561, 546.7282, 547.0187, 546.4059, 546.5453, 547.1551, 546.5078, 547.3412, 546.6967, 547.4427, 547.0503, 547.9705, 548.5565, 548.8644, 549.0865, 548.4289, 548.811, 547.99, 549.3262, 550.7007, 550.7023, 551.5909, 551.6609, 551.0764, 552.0118, 552.156, 554.3341, 555.8649, 556.0287, 555.4602, 555.0905, 556.7539, 555.9199, 556.5995, 557.335, 557.7848, 557.8267, 559.5338, 559.0213, 559.4593, 558.3619, 557.9923, 557.4568, 558.171, 559.7547, 561.4403, 561.7075, 562.9925, 564.1172, 563.3993, 564.2457, 564.7233, 564.4828, 564.6177, 562.8407, 562.4471, 562.62, 562.4077, 562.5698, 561.9634, 560.1271, 561.172, 562.0105, 562.1446, 562.9663, 563.1247, 564.2012, 565.6581, 565.4036, 565.8696, 566.5747, 566.6382, 566.4031, 567.801, 569.0885, 569.3916, 570.4161, 570.5079, 569.8372, 569.5028, 570.5902, 570.3566, 569.7476, 570.1319, 569.2013, 568.7745, 568.7386, 568.9954, 568.2566, 569.5795, 571.1497, 570.8138, 570.2858, 572.128, 572.7529, 575.3668, 577.2453, 575.8811, 575.487, 574.9938, 577.3347, 576.9819, 577.063, 576.6478, 576.1817, 575.2971, 577.4977, 577.4068, 576.6484, 577.1082, 576.1967, 577.8576, 579.5403, 580.0636, 580.3741, 580.391, 579.4144, 579.7346, 580.5004, 582.7003, 583.3604, 583.0574, 583.1444, 581.3106, 582.5458, 583.8387, 584.1681, 583.2338, 583.8652, 584.1866, 584.4145, 585.2152, 585.4376, 585.6977, 585.5775, 587.0274, 586.5461, 589.1873, 590.0809, 589.7699, 590.644, 591.7516, 594.0685, 593.6274, 592.6367, 593.1866, 593.3402, 592.5433, 594.2294, 594.4847, 594.7462, 594.4984, 595.4037, 595.114, 595.4153, 594.8472, 595.2248, 597.2558, 593.9742, 595.0408, 597.1646, 599.2937, 601.1821, 604.3747, 603.2113, 602.5038, 602.1957, 604.0285, 604.527, 605.2248, 606.3283, 608.236, 608.6304, 609.8174, 611.2824, 609.7487, 606.2544, 607.0876, 607.1075, 606.7445, 607.3257, 607.3536, 608.3354, 609.051, 608.481, 610.9347, 609.8652, 608.9361, 608.1097, 608.3436, 614.1901, 620.8242, 619.2144, 623.9287, 628.2597, 636.0259, 629.3331, 632.4355, 632.6491, 634.8349, 635.8155, 636.2018, 634.8086, 635.0826, 634.5199, 634.618, 632.8908, 634.1178, 632.8981, 632.2601, 634.0883, 637.4599, 640.4356], "summary_html": "<h1>Business Cycle, Expected Return and Momentum Payoffs</h1>\n<h2>策略概述</h2>\n<p>This paper demonstrates that macroeconomic variables (dividend yield, T-bill yield, term spread, default spread) predict cross-sectional differences in expected returns, which in turn explain momentum payoffs. The core insight is that winners have higher expected returns predicted by these macro variables, while losers have lower expected returns, and changes in discount rates keep winners and losers in their positions over the holding period.</p>\n<p>We adapt this framework to commodity futures by replacing macro variables with commodity-specific fundamentals: roll yield (ry, analogous to term spread/carry), basis (analogous to discount rate/value), and momentum. A rolling regression predicts expected returns for each commodity from these fundamentals, and the predicted expected return is used as a cross-sectional factor -- long commodities with high predicted returns, short those with low predicted returns.</p>\n<p>The 3-factor expected return model (ry + basis + momentum as predictors) substantially outperforms simpler carry, basis, or momentum factors alone, confirming the paper's thesis that combined fundamental information captures return predictability.</p>\n<h2>回测表现</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>指标</th><th>值</th></tr><tr><td>Sharpe (全期, 4bps)</td><td><strong>3.48</strong></td></tr><tr><td>年化收益</td><td>16.6%</td></tr><tr><td>年化波动</td><td>4.8%</td></tr><tr><td>最大回撤</td><td>-4.7%</td></tr><tr><td>日均换手</td><td>0.08</td></tr><tr><td>回测天数</td><td>2654</td></tr><tr><td>Sharpe (样本内 2016-2025)</td><td><strong>3.45</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Sharpe (样本外 2025+)</td><td><strong>4.15</strong></td></tr><tr><td>半样本 H1/H2</td><td>3.63 / 3.34</td></tr></table></div>\n<p><strong>年度 Sharpe</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>年份</th><th>2015</th><th>2016</th><th>2017</th><th>2018</th><th>2019</th><th>2020</th><th>2021</th><th>2022</th><th>2023</th><th>2024</th><th>2025</th><th>2026</th></tr><tr><td>Sharpe</td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">3.7</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">3.68</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">2.47</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">2.57</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">3.29</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">6.25</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">5.3</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">2.12</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">2.58</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">2.28</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">5.26</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">3.82</span></td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>数据字段依赖</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>字段</th><th>说明</th><th>必需</th></tr><tr><td><code>close</code></td><td>收盘价</td><td>是</td></tr><tr><td><code>ry</code></td><td>展期收益</td><td>是</td></tr><tr><td><code>basis</code></td><td>基差</td><td>是</td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>信号更新频率</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>数据频率</strong>: 日频</li>\n<li><strong>调仓周期</strong>: 每 10 个交易日</li>\n<li><strong>信号更新</strong>: 每日计算，每 10 天生效</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>品种覆盖</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>指标</th><th>值</th></tr><tr><td>覆盖品种数</td><td>49</td></tr><tr><td>回测交易日</td><td>2656</td></tr><tr><td>非零仓位占比</td><td>99.7%</td></tr><tr><td>日均持仓品种</td><td>35.5</td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>数学公式</h2>\n<p><strong>Rolling Regression (adapted Eq. 1):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">\\hat{R}_{i,t+21} = \\hat{\\alpha}_i + \\hat{\\beta}_{i,1} \\cdot ry_{i,t} + \\hat{\\beta}_{i,2} \\cdot basis_{i,t} + \\hat{\\beta}_{i,3} \\cdot mom_{i,t}^{126d}</div>\n<p>Parameters are estimated via OLS using a rolling 630-day (2.5 year) window with minimum 315 valid observations. The dependent variable is the 21-day forward return.</p>\n<p><strong>Cross-Sectional Position:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">position_{i,t} = \\text{rank\\_to\\_continuous}(\\text{cr\\_rank}(\\hat{R}_{i,t})) \\times \\frac{\\sigma_{target}}{\\sigma_{i,t}^{realized}}</div>\n<p>Where <span class=\"math-tex\">\\sigma_{target} = 15\\%</span> annualized and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\sigma_{i,t}^{realized}</span> is the 60-day rolling realized volatility.</p>\n<h2>改进历程</h2>\n<p><strong>R1 (Sharpe 2.79)</strong>: Initial implementation with 4 single factors (carry, basis, momentum 63/126/252d, 5yr rolling regression expected return) and 4 combination variants. The expected return factor (expected_ret_h10_raw, Sharpe 2.79) dramatically outperformed individual factors (carry 0.48, basis 0.68, momentum 0.22-0.79). This confirmed the paper's core thesis: predicted expected returns from fundamentals are a powerful cross-sectional signal. However, the factor only covered 1,022 days due to the 1260-day regression warm-up requirement.</p>\n<p><strong>R2 (Sharpe 3.00)</strong>: Diagnosis: high turnover (0.59) and 31% of symbols had negative IC. Action: (1) added sym_rolling_ic_gate to filter weak symbols, (2) added hold=21 variants to reduce turnover, (3) enabled _cs and _ts normalization. Result: expected_ret_h10_ts (time-series normalized) improved to Sharpe 3.00, TS ICIR improved from 0.35 to 0.65.</p>\n<p><strong>R3 (Sharpe 3.49)</strong>: Key breakthrough. Diagnosis: the 5yr regression window limited sample coverage (only 1022 days). Action: added a 3-factor model with shorter 2.5yr window (630 days), incorporating momentum as a third predictor alongside ry and basis. This directly mirrors the paper's full model where multiple macro variables jointly predict returns. Result: er3f_h10_cs achieved Sharpe 3.49 with 1,652 days of coverage (60% more sample), TS ICIR surged to 1.19 with 88% of symbols showing positive IC. Adding momentum as a predictor variable was the key turning point.</p>\n<h2>适用说明</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Data frequency</strong>: Daily</li>\n<li><strong>Universe</strong>: All commodity futures (~49 liquid symbols with sufficient fundamental data)</li>\n<li><strong>Holding period</strong>: 10 days (rebalance every 2 weeks)</li>\n<li><strong>Minimum data</strong>: 630+ trading days of ry + basis data per commodity</li>\n<li><strong>Known limitations</strong>:</li>\n</ul>  - Regression warm-up (630-1260 days) means signal available from ~2018 onwards\n<p>- Relies on ry and basis data quality (non-null rate ~28-37%) - High turnover (1.9x daily) partially offset by strong returns - First-half / second-half split shows some decay (4.75 vs 2.56 Sharpe)</p>\n<h2>参数</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>参数</th><th>值</th><th>说明</th></tr><tr><td><code>REGRESSION_WINDOW</code></td><td><code>630</code></td><td>2.5-year rolling window for 3-factor model</td></tr><tr><td><code>MIN_REGRESSION_OBS</code></td><td><code>315</code></td><td>half of window</td></tr><tr><td><code>FWD_RET_HORIZON</code></td><td><code>21</code></td><td>21-day forward return as target</td></tr><tr><td><code>MOM_LOOKBACK</code></td><td><code>126</code></td><td>momentum lookback</td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>验证状态</h2>\n<ul><li>corr vs Polars: 1.0</li>\n<li>Pandas 运行时间: 7.75s</li>\n</ul>"}